\cf2 This is a critical architectural conversation. Let me give you my honest assessment as someone who understands both the marketing side and what makes audiobooks actually sell at scale.\
\
Your dev is right, and your instinct was right first. The catalog planner as it stands is a resolver, not an optimizer. That's a real problem when you're trying to produce a credible anxiety series \'97 because listeners browse series the way they browse Netflix. If two books feel structurally identical or thematically redundant, you get refunds and bad reviews, not binge behavior.\
But here's where I'd push back on the dev's plan slightly, from a market perspective:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf2 The 12-topic anxiety lattice is good but needs market validation\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 That list (social anxiety, panic attacks, health anxiety, etc.) is clinically sound. But from an audiobook marketing standpoint, some of those topics are massive standalone markets and others are niche subtopics that work better as angles within a broader book. For example:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Social anxiety, panic attacks, overthinking/rumination, and sleep anxiety \'97 these are each big enough to be standalone books with their own search volume on Audible, their own Reddit communities, their own ad audiences. These deserve full-length, arc-driven books.\
\ls4\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Driving/travel anxiety, authority/conflict anxiety, somatic symptom fear loop \'97 these are real but niche. They work better as mid-length books or as angle variants on a broader anxiety book. A listener searching "anxiety audiobook" won't find "driving anxiety" \'97 but a listener who bought your general anxiety book might convert on a targeted follow-up.\
\ls4\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Public speaking anxiety crosses into the performance/professional development category, which means different persona targeting, different keywords, different ad creative.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 So the lattice shouldn't just be a flat list. It needs a market tier:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Tier 1 (standalone series anchors): Social anxiety, panic/anxiety attacks, overthinking, sleep anxiety, health anxiety\
\ls5\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Tier 2 (strong mid-length or series installments): Work performance anxiety, relationship anxiety, anticipatory anxiety\
\ls5\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
