\fs36 \cf2 What This Means for Production Sequencing\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 Don't build all 1,008 titles in parallel. Build the flagships first:\
Month 1-2: 10 flagship general titles (your top 5 topics \'d7 2 arc variants each). Full atom pools, human narration, active marketing.\
Month 2-4: 50 persona variants of those flagships (5 topics \'d7 3 personas \'d7 3-4 angle variants). AI narration. Ride the flagship marketing.\
Month 4-8: Scale to full persona \'d7 topic grid. 200+ titles. AI narration. Wide distribution.\
Month 8-12: Long tail expansion. Subtopic variants, angle variants, location variants. Fill the catalog to 1,000+.\
This is the same total output but front-loads what actually generates revenue and discovery. The data you just showed me confirms this is the right sequence \'97 persona titles need flagships to draft behind, not the other way around.\
