\fs32 \cf2 \cb7 Implication for the planner: Every book must be compilable, purchasable, and therapeutically complete without reference to any other book. The series wrapper provides metadata inheritance and catalog organization \'97 not narrative dependency.\cb1 \
\cb7 The Four Non-Negotiable Standalone Rules\cb1 \
\cb7 Rule 1: No "Previously in This Series" Content. Each book assumes zero prior reading. The listener found this book through TikTok. They've never heard of the series.\cb1 \
\cb7 Rule 2: Each Book Owns a Search Term. Every book maps to a real query people type into Audible, Google, or TikTok. If a book doesn't own a search term, fold it into another book as a chapter. The consumer_language_map.yaml governs which terms each topic owns.\cb1 \
\cb7 Rule 3: Different Valuable Information Per Book. Same mechanism, different engine. Same persona, different world. Same arc shape, different emotional terrain. The "cocktail party test": a listener should describe two books as obviously different.\cb1 \
\cb7 Rule 4: Audible Algorithm Compatibility. Each book must have: unique title+subtitle, unique ISBN, distinct BISAC subcategory placement where possible, and unique keyword set. No two books from the same brand should compete for identical keywords.\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

